                    "body": "Resolved in trunk and 1.5 release branch by r9324",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-25T16:15:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-25T16:15:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30911",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=electricowl",
                        "name": "electricowl",
                        "displayName": "Ian Lewis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I really take issue with this. It is poor design and breaks the model for those of us building forms with checkboxes. \n\nIf I wanted a hidden element then I should be able to extend the form checkbox to add it in, it's not rocket science. Unfortunately it does take some serious surgery to get rid of a hidden checkbox inserted without my even knowing about it.\n\nIt is a bad idea because:\nwhen working with the DOM in JavaScript a hidden element with the same name creates an array of elements. \nOne of the effects of this is that a simple - \n  if (oForm.my_checkbox.checked) will return undefined instead of true or false. \n changing it to if (oForm.my_checkbox[1].checked) should be my decision not one imposed on me.\n\nThe correct behaviour should be that an unchecked (unticked) checkbox should return no value on submit. \nIt should be an option and not require a workaround.\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=electricowl",
                        "name": "electricowl",
                        "displayName": "Ian Lewis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-12T09:08:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-12T09:08:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30912",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=andy.wenk",
                        "name": "andy.wenk",
                        "displayName": "Andreas Wenk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "\"If I wanted a hidden element then I should be able to extend the form checkbox to add it in, it's not rocket science.\"\n\nHaving the possibility to set a parameter in the attribs would be the best way to handle it. I fully agree.\n\nIn most cases it is good to get a value also from a checkbox. Submitting a form with a input field results always in recieving the field - if it's empty or not. So why not having this behaviour with all form fields?\nTo have full conformity with the HTML specs you are right if you expect the behaviour you described ('cause that's the way it is in HTML). The intention to have the hiodden field in this helper was because I always find it annoying when a checkbopx does not submit a value.  \n\nCheers\n\nAndy",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=andy.wenk",
                        "name": "andy.wenk",
                        "displayName": "Andreas Wenk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-12T10:12:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-12T10:12:01.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
